I’ve said repeatedly that Judge Kavanaugh is eminently qualified to serve on the Supreme Court. I proudly voted to advance his nomination today, and I will vote to officially confirm him tomorrow.

I join all Americans in welcoming the news that Pastor Andrew Brunson has finally been released from his unjust detention.

I speak for all Hoosiers in condemning these hateful and cowardly acts in the strongest terms. We are all Americans and any attempted attack on our fellow citizens is an attack on all of us.

Mark Lowcock, Under-Secretary-General for Humanitarian Affairs and Emergency Relief Coordinator, at #UNSC yesterday: Half of Yemen’s population—14 million people—could soon confront pre-famine conditions.  His speech is worth reading:  https://t.co/1Qmsy1PxPu

He says, “The parties to the conflict continue to violate international humanitarian law. Since late May, more than 5,000 separate violations have been recorded, including mass civilian casualties and destruction or damage to critical civilian infrastructure…”

The administration’s NDAA Section 1290 certification is not consistent with these facts:  https://t.co/DApUvEd9U7.  I look forward to responses from the administration to our letter: 
https://t.co/f05j1JoakM
We need to use all available leverage to compel both sides to pursue good faith and urgent diplomatic efforts to end the civil war in Yemen.

I thank Attorney General Sessions for his distinguished public service to the nation. I look forward to reviewing the qualifications of President Trump’s nominee for Attorney General.
I’m hosting U.S. Secretary of Labor @SecretaryAcosta in Indiana today to discuss apprenticeships, workforce development, and retirement security. https://t.co/9ICfQeENgL

One of our first stops is @GaylorElectric in Noblesville. Gaylor Electric’s #apprenticeship program is one example of how work-based learning benefits both businesses and Americans entering the workforce in today’s economy. https://t.co/5SfhAL31on

America faces a skills gap as technological advances continue to transform the workforce. We are discussing ways to better prepare Americans with the skills needed for 21st century jobs. https://t.co/5YYDwyLvjW

Because of #taxreform, @GaylorElectric was able to invest their savings in a mobile innovation center that provides on-the-go and on-the-spot training to students and electricians at their projects. https://t.co/B2oQCI0qMA

Just left @indianastate in Terre Haute where @SecretaryAcosta and I spoke about retirement security. More than 40 million people do not have access to any workplace retirement plan. We discussed ways to help Hoosiers save for the future. https://t.co/GFGAtBzkpc
Honoring our veterans in Indianapolis today. https://t.co/RUOUKK99ma
